How to setup Easy PHP Framework (EPF)

Step 1:
 - download from http://www.bison.hu
 - or
 - clone from github: git://github.com/itarato/easy-php-framework.git
 - copy it to a folder at your webroot, like /var/www/ef_project_1/
 
Step 2:
 - get Doctrine: http://www.doctrine-project.org/
 - copy to ef_project_1/class/lib/Doctrine, so you can find Doctrine.php at
   ef_project_1/class/lib/Doctrine/lib/Doctrine.php
 
Step 3:
 - create a database
 
Step 4:
 - customize your database settings in setup.php at project root
 
Step 5:
 - make sure rewrite_mod enabled by apache2
 
Step 6:
 - write your browsers search bar: localhost/ef_project_1/
 
 
Requirements:
 - apache 2
 - php 5.2
 - php pdo
 - mysql 5 / postgresql 8 / sqlite 2 ...
 
More details at http://www.bison.hu

